      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "A typical recent example is a study by [CITATION_1] , in which 12 patients who presented at Mount Sinai Medical Center in Miami Beach with exercise-induced asthma during the last half of 1992 (and who in addition were selected on the basis of a number of intake criteria) were randomized into three groups of size four, one group receiving heparin, another cromolyn sodium, the third a placebo. A statistically signi cant di erence between the groups was found, in favor of heparin, and both the abstract (\\Inhaled heparin prevents exercise-induced asthma without in uencing histamine-induced bronchoconstriction\") and the discussion section of the paper read as if there is no longer any uncertainty about how everybody with this ailment should be treated."
